HEADWORD: Salty
<hw>Salt"y</hw> <pr>(s⟦add⟧lt"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Containing salt; tasting of salt; saltish; <as>as, the
<ex>salty</ex> sea; the potatoes are too <ex>salty</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Interesting and witty; piquant; -- of
